@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title State Machine - marketplace/AcceptedAgreement
skinparam state {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
}
left to right direction
hide empty description
state "Observe" as observe
state "EvaluateReady" as evaluate_ready
state "Ready" as ready
state "Retryable" as retryable
state "Failed" as failed
observe : read spec, tracked status, delete intent,\nand current OCI lifecycle
state "ResolveByLookup" as resolve_by_lookup
state "RejectUnsupportedDrift" as reject_unsupported_drift
state "ApplyUpdate" as apply_update
state "DeletePending" as delete_pending
state "Deleted" as deleted
state "DeleteCleanupBlocked" as delete_cleanup_blocked
[*] --> observe : CreateAcceptedAgreement
observe --> resolve_by_lookup : tracked identity missing
resolve_by_lookup --> evaluate_ready : lookup or create reaches\nACTIVE
resolve_by_lookup --> failed : unresolved OCI error or non-success state
observe --> evaluate_ready : OCI state in ACTIVE
observe --> failed : unresolved OCI error or non-success state
evaluate_ready --> reject_unsupported_drift : force-new or conflicting\ndrift detected
reject_unsupported_drift --> ready : wait for spec or live state change
evaluate_ready --> apply_update : supported mutable drift for\ndefined_tags, display_name,\nfreeform_tags
apply_update --> ready : update path completes
evaluate_ready --> ready : no supported drift remains
ready --> ready : no supported drift remains
retryable --> retryable : OCI remains retryable
failed --> failed : OCI remains terminal
ready --> delete_pending : delete requested
retryable --> delete_pending : delete requested
failed --> delete_pending : delete requested
delete_pending --> delete_cleanup_blocked : cleanup or finalizer release remains blocked
delete_cleanup_blocked --> deleted : retry delete completion until allowed
deleted --> deleted : terminal stutter
note right of ready
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-controller-state-machine.svg
Start from the shared controller phase model and
specialize imported provider states, delete
targets, and failure exits here.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers map provider states into the shared
controller phases with explicit finalizer and
requeue policies.
service: marketplace
slug: acceptedagreement
kind: AcceptedAgreement
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required /
retain-until-confirmed-delete
requeue: terminating
provider states: create none; update none;
delete none
supported drift: defined_tags, display_name,
freeform_tags
reject before mutate: force-new fields
agreement_id, compartment_id, listing_id,
package_version (+1 more)
create-only fields: none
list lookup: oci_marketplace_accepted_agreements
filters agreement_id, compartment_id,
display_name, listing_id (+1 more)
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
AcceptedAgreement reuses an existing OCI
agreement before create by exact compartmentId,
listingId, packageVersion, and agreementId
match, with displayName narrowing when set.
OCI accepted agreement responses do not expose
lifecycle state, so successful create and update
normalize directly to Active from the immediate
response body.
In-place updates are limited to displayName,
definedTags, and freeformTags; agreementId,
compartmentId, listingId, packageVersion, and
signature are replacement-only.
The controller mirrors the last applied
signature at status.appliedSignature because OCI
read models never return the signature needed
for explicit drift checks.
Delete retains the finalizer until
DeleteAcceptedAgreement is followed by
GetAcceptedAgreement returning not found.
end note
note right of delete_pending
delete policy: required
delete observe: GetAcceptedAgreement or
ListAcceptedAgreements
delete targets: DELETED
end note
@enduml
